[[File:Daan Viljoen Nature Reserve.jpg|thumb|Daan Viljoen Nature Reserve, main building, 2017]]
'''Daan Viljoen Game Reserve''' is a [[game reserve]] near [[Windhoek]], [[Namibia]]. It is situated in the hill area of [[Khomas Hochland]].<ref name="TonchiLindeke2012">{{cite book|last1=Tonchi|first1=Victor L.|last2=Lindeke|first2=William A.|last3=Grotpeter|first3=John J.|title=Historical Dictionary of Namibia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VUkGQ6xfYkgC&pg=PA69|date=31 August 2012|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-7990-4|pages=69–}}</ref>
The park has many walking paths and allows tourists to travel around by themselves. The park is a good example of the [[wildlife of Namibia]]. It is named for [[Daniel Thomas du Plessis Viljoen]] (1892–1972), the [[South Africa]]n [[List of colonial governors of South West Africa|administrator of South West Africa]] from 1953 to 1963.

