{{Main|Mountain peaks of Canada}} The vast majority of [[mountain]]s in [[Canada]] lie in the western provinces of [[British Columbia]], [[Alberta]], and the [[Yukon]] Territory. Mountains can be found all over British Columbia while those in Alberta are mainly situated on the eastern side of the [[Canadian Rockies]]. The [[Saint Elias Mountains]] in the Yukon hold some of country's highest mountains, including the highest, [[Mount Logan]] at 5,959 meters.
