{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}} '''Rione''' ({{IPA-it|riˈoːne}}; plural: ''rioni'') is the name given to a neighbourhood in several Italian cities. A ''rione'' is a territorial subdivision. The larger administrative subdivisions in Rome are the [[Municipi_of_Rome#Municipi|Municipi]], with the rioni being used only in the historic centre. The word derives from the {{lang-la|regiones}}, the 14 subdivisions of Rome imposed by [[Augustus]].<ref name=treccani>{{it}} [http://www.treccani.it/vocabolario/rione/ The word rione] in the [[Treccani]] dictionary on-line</ref> The term has been adopted as a synonym of [[quartiere]] in the Italian [[comune|comuni]].<ref name=treccani/>
==See also== * [[Rioni of Rome]] * [[Frazione]] * [[Località]] * [[Circoscrizione]] * [[Terziere]] * [[Quartiere]] * [[Sestiere]]
