{{Infobox settlement | name = Siddhirganj | settlement_type = City | pushpin_map = Bangladesh | pushpin_label_position = right | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Bangladesh | coordinates = {{coord|23|41|N|90|31|E|region:BD|display=inline}} | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{flag|Bangladesh}} | subdivision_type1 = [[Divisions of Bangladesh|Division]] | subdivision_type2 = [[Districts of Bangladesh|District]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Dhaka Division]] | subdivision_name2 = [[Narayanganj District]] | government_type = Narayanganj City Corporation | area_total_km2 = 22.71 | population_total = 256760 | postal_code = 1430 }}
'''Siddhirganj''', is one of the oldest industrial cities of [[Bangladesh]]. It is located in the bank of [[Shitalakshya River]], [[Narayanganj District|Narayanganj]]. The Siddhirganj Industrial Zone has more than 15 thousand factories and industrial establishments. [[Adamjee Jute Mills|Adamjee Jute Mill]]<nowiki/>s was established in Siddhirganj in 1951 and was once the [http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/2065044.stm largest jute mill] in the world. From 2005 to 2016, the Adamjee [[Bangladesh Export Processing Zone Authority|export processing zone]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bepza.gov.bd/pages/epzdetails/adamjee-export-processing-zone-2/location-3|title=Location of Adamjee Export processing Zone|last=|first=|date=|website=bepza.gov.bd|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> in Siddhirganj<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://siddhirganj.com/adamjee-epz-siddhirganj/|title=Adamjee EPZ Profile|last=|first=|date=|website=Siddhirganj.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> exported more than 2251.19 million US dollars' worth of garments items.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bepza.gov.bd/exports/export_report/adamjee-export-processing-zone-2|title=Year Wise Export|last=|first=|date=|website=Info Of Adamjee EPZ|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
== History == From ancient times Siddhirganj was famous for its rich textile Industry. Due to its favorable geographic location Siddhirganj was historically used as a port city and specialized in muslin production from hand looms. As a gateway to [[Dhaka]], [[Narayanganj Sadar Upazila|Narayanganj's]] economic activities were largely contributed by Siddhirganj and it was also called the [[Dundee]] of the East.
The traditional art of weaving [[Muslin|Jamdani muslin]] in Bangladesh was included in the list of [[Masterpieces of the Oral and Intangible Heritage of Humanity]] by UNESCO. In the [[Bangladesh Liberation War|liberation war of Bangladesh]], war hero [[Shafi Imam Rumi]]'s major target was to bomb the Siddhirganj Power Station.
== Power station == Siddhirganj has four power stations<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.egcb.com.bd/welcome/plant_details/1|title=egcb.com.bd|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> total and manufacturing more than 400 MW in electricity generation capacity.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://projects.worldbank.org/P095965/siddhirganj-peaking-power-project?lang=en|title=Siddhirganj Power Project|last=|first=|date=|website=worldbank.org|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://siddhirganj.com/siddhirganj-power-project/|title=Siddhirganj Power Project|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> A new power station called the Siddhirganj Peaking Power Project is set to be completed by 30 June 2018 after 10 years of construction at a total cost of $470 million.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://projects.worldbank.org/P095965/siddhirganj-peaking-power-project?lang=en|title=Projects : Siddhirganj Power Project {{!}} The World Bank|website=projects.worldbank.org|access-date=2017-10-30}}</ref>
